originalText.text: This was a solid experience all the way around. Although this place is pretty wide open, it was not super noisy. The music was at a reasonable volume.  Most of the food we had was good but not great with some notable exceptions.  The sashimi tuna was incredible. Very fresh and tasty.  The Rosemary crisps we're a nice starter.  And, The churro with salted caramel ice cream was a great finish, mainly the ice cream.  The remaining items, the often well reviewed cornbread, the burger, the hanger steak, and the salmon were all fine.  Drink menu was solid, and I enjoyed the watermelon margarita. I would certainly go back but I would order the items I noted above.

originalText.text: We visited for Thanksgiving dinner since we were in NY for the parade. Sweetbriar is an awesome place. The staff are so nice and helpful. It happened to be my wife's significant birthday, and they came to the table with two glasses of wine to celebrate. That was very thoughtful and much appreciated. Lastly, the food was the best part. Everything tasted amazing. I don't eat brussel sprouts at all, but the way they prepared them, I ate every single one. The proportions were more than enough. Thank you for making a great day even more amazing.

originalText.text:
Service was okay, and the food was not great. Restaurant was surprisingly empty for Saturday at 6:30 PM, but the food took a while to come out.

We ordered a cocktail, cornbread with honey butter, mushroom pizza, and the sweetbriar burger.
- Cocktail was non memorable
- The honey butter that came with the cornbread was the star of the show.
- The burger was fine albeit messy -- my assumption is that the burger was assembled when the patty was still too hot because the sauce was loose and runny. If this is the normal, I would have appreciated extra napkins as a precaution.
- The pizza was served to us raw. Even looking back at the photo, I don't know how it left the kitchen. This was the moment our hearts sank, and we asked the server to take it back.

Our server was really apologetic when they realized that the pizza was still in fact raw. The manager came by to also apologize and ensure that it would be taken off the tab. When asked about everything else, I gave her my honest feedback about the burger, and she was defensive. The only thing they did to fix the night was offer to comp the raw pizza that we couldn't eat, and that's as far as the apology went.

I tried to contact them the next day after I processed the situation, and we were left on read.

originalText.text:
Such a beautiful, cozy and elegant environment. The bar area is gorgeous and I love the fact that there's an open kitchen. But, most importantly: the food is delicious. Here are my choices:

Starters:
- Rosemary crisps is light and refreshing , perfect for sharing.
- The cornbread is among the best I've ever had.
Main:
- The burger is so juicy, full of flavors - and the side potatoes are so good, the aioli is the cherry on top.
- The ribs have a spicy touch, love that.
Dessert -
a tart with pistachios and berries, love the balance, it was not super sweet.

originalText.text: Fabulous experience. Bartender "in the photo" was amazing. Go see him for some amazing drinks.  The staff was accommodating with my sister in her wheelchair and as you can see I suggest the margaritas pizza. Delish!!!!  Will definitely be back!!
